Question 3.1.14 (Optimal Control - Minimum Principle)

Sequence: (u0, u1,...,u_{N-1})

Function #1: g(x_n) = sum_0_{N-1} [g(x_i,u_i]

Constraints: x_{i+1} = f_i(x,u) where u is real

Hamiltonian: H(x,u,p_{i+1}) = g(x,u) + p*f(x,u)

Terminal Condition: p_i*=d/dx[H(x*,u*,p*)]

Rule: Proposition 3.1.1:
        a) f(x*)(x-x*) >= 0
        b) If f is convex over X, then x* minimizes X


